{
    "id": "384",
    "title": "Modified Early Warning Score (MEWS) for Clinical Deterioration",
    "desc": "The Modified Early Warning Score (MEWS) etermines the degree of illness of a patient using 4 physiological findings and one observation.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11588210",
                "text": "Subbe CP, Kruger M, Rutherford P, Gemmel L. Validation of a modified Early Warning Score in medical admissions. QJM. 2001 Oct;94(10):521-6."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1963767/",
                "text": "Gardner-Thorpe J, Love N, Wrightson J, Walsh S, Keeling N. The Value of Modified Early Warning Score (MEWS) in surgical in-patients: a prospective observational study. Ann R Coll Surg Engl. 2006;88(6):571–575."
            }
        ],
        "evidence": "<p>Addition of the selected points; points assigned below:</p>",
        "facts": "<p>See formula table; below:</p>\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\n<table class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th><strong>Criteria</strong></th>\n<th><strong>Point Value</strong></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Systolic BP (mmHg)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&le;70</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>71-80</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>81-100</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>101-199</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&ge;200</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Heart rate (beats per minute)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&lt;40</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>41-50</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>51-100</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>101-110</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>11-129</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&gt;130</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Respiratory rate (breaths per minute)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&lt;9</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9-14</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>15-20</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>21-29</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&gt;30</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Temperature in &deg;C (&deg;F)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&lt;35 (&lt;95)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>35.0&ndash;38.4 (95&ndash;101.12)</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&gt;38.5 (101.3)</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><strong>AVPU</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Alert?</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Voice?</td>\n<td>+1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pain?</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Unresponsive?</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Interpretation</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A score &ge;5 is statistically linked to increased likelihood of death or admission to an intensive care unit.</li>\n<li>For any single physiological parameter scored +3, consider higher level of care for patient.</li>\n</ul>",
        "estimation": [],
